@endnode

@node MN_PROJ "Menu:  Project"
@prev MENUS

@{u}@{b}Project:@{ub}@{uu}
  - New - Clears the database.
          @{b}HotKey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> N

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Open - Loads a new database.  If the @{"Edit Type" link GUI_ETYP} is "Text" an ASCII text
          file may be loaded.
          @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> O

  - Insert - Inserts new data into the current database.  New records are
            inserted above the current record.  New fields (if used) are
            appended to the end of the field list.
             See the @{"Settings->Insert/Append" link MN_STNG} menu for options relating to how
            the new data is handled.

             If the @{"edit type" link GUI_ETYP} is "Text", a requester will appear asking if
            you wish to insert new data into the current database,or ASCII
            text into the current text.
            @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> I

  - Append - Appends new data into the current database.  New records and
            fields will be appended to the end of their respective lists.
             See the @{"Settings->Insert/Append" link MN_STNG} menu for options relating to how
            the new data is handled.

             ASCII text may also be appended if editing multi-line text.
            @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> +

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Save - Saves the database using the current file name (unless "unnamed").
           @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> S

  - Save As - Brings up a file requester to save the database.  If the
             @{"Edit Type" link GUI_ETYP} is "Text" then just the text may be saved as an ASCII
             file.
             @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> A

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - About - Guess.  :-)
            @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> ?

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Quit - Another toughie.  Will ask for verification if your work hasn't yet
          been saved.
          @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> Q
@endnode

@node MN_EDIT "Menu:  Edit"

@{u}@{b}Edit:@{ub}@{uu}
  - Execute - Takes the appropriate action (or inaction) depending on the
             field type (see @{"field types" link FLDTYP} for more info.).
             @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> E

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Select All - All titles are selected.
                 @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> L


  - Select None - All titles are deselected.
                  @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> 0

  - Toggle - Selected titles aren't, & unselected titles are.  :-)
             @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> =

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Cut - Moves selected items to the clipboard.
          @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> X

  - Copy - Copies selected items to the clipboard.
           @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> C

  - Paste - Inserts the contents of the current clipboard unit.  Contents are
           inserted above the currently selected item.
           @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> V

  - Unit - Selects the current clipboard unit (0 - 10)to use for cutting,
          copying, and pasting.

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Edit - Chooses the @{"Edit Type" link GUI_ETYP}; just like the Edit cycle gadget For those
          who don't use CycleToMenu (why?! :-) ).

  - Mode - Selects the @{"Edit Mode" link GUI_EMOD}; same as the gadget.  See Edit Modes for more
          info.

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Undelete - The last item deleted is restored, & placed after the current
              item.  An index (".001" ...) will be appended to the restored
              item in the event another item shares the restored item's name.
              @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> U

  - Flush - Clears the undelete buffer of the current Edit Type (each Edit
           Type has its own undelete buffer).

  - Flush All - Clears ALL undelete buffers.
@endnode

@node MN_SRCH "Menu:  Search"

@{u}@{b}Search:@{ub}@{uu}
  - Set Pattern - Brings up the search requester to set the current
                 search pattern.
                 @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> P

  - Find Next - Finds the next occurence of the current search pattern.
                @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> ]

  - Find Prev - Finds the previous occurence of the current search pattern.
                @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> [

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  @{u}@{b}Ignore:@{ub}@{uu}
    - Case - Searches are case insensitive ("A" = "a") if this item is
            checked.

    - Titles - For records only.  The title of a record is ignored; only its
              data is searched for the current pattern.

    - Text - For records only.  If checked, multiline text (@{"field type" link FLDTYP}
            "TEXT") is ignored during searches.

  @{u}@{b}Scan Only:@{ub}@{uu}
    - Titles - For records only.  When checked, only a record's title is
              matched against the search pattern.

    - Selected Items - Only selected items are searched.

    - Selected Fields - For records only.  Only the fields that are selected
                       (in Edit:  Fields) are matched against the search
                       pattern if this item is checked.  Otherwise all fields
                       of a record are scanned.
@endnode

@node MN_SORT "Menu:  Sort"

@{u}@{b}Sort:@{ub}@{uu}
  - Sort - Sorts the current Edit Type list.
           @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> T

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Ignore Case - "A" = "a".  This slows the sort somewhat.

  - Sort By Title - Only for records.  The list of records is sorted by title
                   when this menu item is checked.  Otherwise the list is
                   sorted using the current field.

  - Only Selected - Do you wish to sort all items, or just the selected ones?

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Reverse - Reverses the order of the current Edit Type list.  Takes the
             "Ignore Case" and "Only Selected" menu items into account.
             @{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  <R. Amiga> R
@endnode

@node MN_STNG "Menu:  Settings"
@next MENUS

@{u}@{b}Settings:@{ub}@{uu}

  @{u}@{b}Insert/Append:@{ub}@{uu}
    - Ignore New Fields? - No new fields will be added to the field list.

    These options tell ShimmerDB what to do if it encounters a record with
    the same name as an existing record.
    - Use Old Record - The new record is ignored.
    - Use New Record - Data from the old record is discarded and replaced with
                      data from the new record.
    - Index New Record - The new record will be renamed to something like
                        <record name>.001.

  ~~~~~~~~~~

  - Create Icons? - If checked, a database is saved with a project icon.
                    The current dimensions of ShimmerDB's GUI (width, height,
                    etc.) are also saved as @{"tooltypes" link START}.
@endnode

@node GUI_TBAR "ShimmerDB GUI:  Title Bar"
@prev MAINGUI

@{b}---------------------------------------------
|o| Record: @{ub}A. Rexx@{b}  Field: @{ub}Address     @{b}|'|#|
|-------------------------------------------|@{ub}

The title bar displays the current record and field.
@endnode

@node GUI_POS "ShimmerDB GUI:  Position Gadget"
     @{b}____
Pos:|   @{ub}2@{b}| /@{ub} 3
     @{b}----@{ub}

  Displays your position, and the total number of items, in the current list.
You may jump to any position by entering a number in the integer gadget.
@endnode

@node GUI_FILE "ShimmerDB GUI:  Filename Gadget"
       @{b}________________
File: |@{ub}RAM:SmegDB      @{b}|
       ----------------@{ub}

The path and name of the database file you're editing.
@endnode

@node GUI_ETYP "ShimmerDB GUI:  Edit-Type Cycle Gadget"
       @{b}_________
Edit: |@|@{ub}Records@{b}|
       ---------@{ub}

Selects which list type to edit.  Possible choices:

- Fields  - Fields are the building blocks of any database.  They are the
           categories each object in your database possesses.  For instance,
           if you're creating an address book you would have fields such as
           "Name", "Address", "Phone", "E-Mail", etc.
           Fields may also hold multiple lines of text, and be set to execute
           commands.  See @{"field types" link FLDTYP} for more information.

- Records - A record is a collection of fields.  Using the address book
           example, each person would be a record, and have its own "Name"
           field, "Address" field, etc.

- Text    - Multiple lines of text may be entered in the Edit listview gadget.
           Such text is associated with the record and field displayed in the
           @{"title bar" link GUI_TBAR}.

@{b}Note:@{ub}
  - Field and record names are case-sensitive.  "ReadMe" and "readme" are seen
   as different names.

  - If you enter a field or record name that has already been used, an index
   will be appended to it.  For example, continually entering "readme" would
   result in the names: "readme", "readme.001", "readme.002", etc.


@{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  e         (cycle forwards),
         <Shift> e (cycle backwards)
@endnode

@node GUI_FLV "ShimmerDB GUI:  Edit Listview"
@{b} ________________
| @{ub}Name@{b}          ||
| @{ub}Address@{b}       ||@{ub}

  The edit listview displays the the titles of fields and records, and also
multi-line text.

  Multiple items may be selected by holding down the <SHIFT> key.
@endnode

@node GUI_LVSTR "ShimmerDB GUI:  Edit String Gadget"
 @{b}_______________
|@{ub}D. Lister@{b}      |
 ---------------@{ub}

  Data entered here will be added to the @{"edit listview" link GUI_FLV}.  The way it is added
depends on the current @{"edit mode" link GUI_EMOD}.

  Pressing <TAB> switches the cursor to the first field string gadget.
@endnode

@node GUI_EMOD "ShimmerDB GUI:  Edit Mode Gadget"
 @{b}___________
|@|   @{ub}Add@{b}   |
 -----------@{ub}

  The edit mode gadget affects how mouse clicks in the edit listview or text
entered in the sdit string gadget will be processed.

@{b}Edit modes:@{ub}
  - Add - Any text entered in the edit string gadget is appended to the end of
         the current list.
          Duplicate field and record names will have an index appended to them
         (e.g.  E-Mail Address.001)

  - Edit - The selected item's name will be copied to the edit string gadget
          where it may be edited.

  - Insert - Like "Add", only the text entered will be inserted above the
            currently selected item.

  - Duplicate - Any items clicked on in the edit listview will be duplicated,
               and an index will be appended (unless editing text).

               NOTE:  Only the item's name is duplicated.  Duplicating a
               record, for example, will not also duplicate any data contained
               within the record.

  - Move Above - Moves selected items in the edit listview above an item.
                Select an item (or items) in the edit list view, and then
                click where (in the listview :-) ) you wish them to be moved
                too.  The selected item(s) will be moved above the entry
                clicked on.

  - Move Below - Works the same as "Move Above", only now the selected items
                will be located below the entry clicked on.


@{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  m         (cycle forwards),
         <Shift> m (cycle backwards)
@endnode

@node GUI_DEL "ShimmerDB GUI:  Delete Gadget"
 @{b}___
|@{ub}Del@{b}|
 ---@{ub}

  The delete button will delete all items selected in the edit listview.

  Use the Edit->Undelete menu option to retrieve deleted data.  Each list
maintains its own undelete buffer (currently 100 items).  Once the undelete
buffer is full, the oldest item will be discarded (& gone for good) to make
room for each newly-deleted item.
@endnode

@node GUI_VSLD "ShimmerDB GUI:  View Slider"
 @{b}________
|   o    |
 --------@{ub}

  This slider gadget determines how much of the horizontal space in ShimmerDB's
window is occupied by the edit listview and the field views (oh, just try it
and see for yourself :-)  ).
  With the knob all the way to the left, the field views will get the lion's
share of the available window real estate.  All the way to the right gives the
nod to the edit listview.  Somewhere in between lies perfection (perfection's
a liar?!  Hmmm, could be... (How many other program docs tackle the tough
philosophical issues, eh?  :-) (Erm, now you know why.  :-) ))).
@endnode

@node GUI_FLD "ShimmerDB GUI:  Field Data String Gadget"
       @{b} _______________
Name   |@{ub}@{uu}Ima Goof@{b}       |
        ---------------@{ub}

  The data for each field is entered here.  If editing records, pressing
<CTRL> <RETURN> will execute the field type (see @{"field types" link FLDTYP}).

  <TAB> cycles between the various field data string gadgets and the edit
string gadget.
@endnode

@node GUI_NSLD "ShimmerDB GUI:  Field Slider"
@next MAINGUI
 @{b}________
|  o     |
 --------@{ub}

  Divides horizontal space in field view, in the same manner as the
@{"view slider" link GUI_VSLD}.  Sets how much space is devoted to the field
names and field data.
@endnode

@node SRCHLV "Search GUI:  Set Pattern"
@prev SRCHGUI
 @{b}__________________
|@{ub}B?gg*@{b}            ||
|                 ||
|------------------|
|@{ub}*ll*@{b}              |
 ------------------@{ub}

  Enter a new search pattern in the string gadget, or retrieve a pattern from
the listview.  The pattern displayed in the string gadget is the current
search pattern.

  Search patterns may contain AmigaDOS pattern matching @{"wildcards" link WLDPAT}.
@endnode

@node SRCHNXT "Search GUI:  Find Next Button"
 @{b}________
|  @{ub}Next@{b}  |
 --------@{ub}

Finds the next occurence of the current search pattern.


@{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  N
@endnode

@node SRCHPRV "Search GUI:  Find Previous Button"
 @{b}________
|@{ub}Previous@{b}|
 --------@{ub}

Finds the previous occurence of the current search pattern.


@{b}Hotkey:@{ub}  P
@endnode

@node IGNR "Search GUI:  Ignore Options"
 @{b}--Ignore---
||  | Case  |
||  | Titles|
||  | Text  |
 -----------@{ub}

Ignore:
  - Case - Searches are case insensitive ("A" = "a") if this item is
          checked.

  - Titles - For records only.  The title of a record is ignored; only its
            data is searched for the current pattern.

  - Text - For records only.  If checked, multiline text (@{"field type" link FLDTYP}
          "TEXT") is ignored during searches.
@endnode

@node SCAN "Search GUI:  Scan Options"
 @{b}-----Scan Only------
||  | Titles         |
||  | Selected Items |
||  | Selected Fields|
 --------------------@{ub}

Scan Only:
  - Titles - For records only.  When checked, only a record's title is
            matched against the search pattern.

  - Selected Items - Only selected items are searched.

  - Selected Fields - For records only.  Only the fields that are selected
                     (in Edit:  Fields) are matched against the search
                     pattern if this item is checked.  Otherwise all fields
                     of a record are scanned.
@endnode

@node CLRPAT "Search GUI:  Clear Pattern List"
@next SRCHGUI
 @{b}_____________
|@{ub}Clear Pattern@{b}|
 -------------@{ub}

Clears all search patterns in the @{"search pattern listview" link SRCHLV}.
@endnode

@node WLDPAT "AmigaDOS Pattern Matching"
@prev SRCHLV
@next WLDPAT

A brief summary of important AmigaDOS pattern matching wildcards:
     (What, you don't already know these?!  :-)  )

  #? (or "*", if enabled) - Match any characters.

  ?                       - Match a single character.

  #<p>                    - Match zero or more occurrences of <p>.

  ~(<p>)                  - Do not match <p>.

  (<p1>|<p2>)             - Logical OR - Match <p1> or <p2>

  (<char>-<char>)         - Set a character range (e.g. (A-E))
@endnode

@node LIMITS "ShimmerDB:  Limits"
@prev SRCHGUI

@{b}Maximum number of:@{ub}
  - Fields,
    Records,
    Lines of multi-line text,
    Search patterns:                  65,500 *, **

  - Characters in a string gadget:    256 **, ***

  - Items in undelete buffer:         100 **

  - Clipboard buffers:                10 (units 0 - 9) **


  *    Also limited by the amount of free memory.

  **   Arbitrary.  This may be expanded or user definable in future versions.

  ***  If ASCII text is loaded, lines with more than 256 characters are
      truncated.  Future versions may/should split the line.
@endnode

@node FORM "ShimmerDB:  File Format"

@{u}@{b}File Format:@{ub}@{uu}
  ShimmerDB saves databases in an IFF format consisting of three FORMS and
three chunks.  Note:  This format is still under construction (as is it's
explanation  :-)  ).

@{b}Forms:@{ub}
  - SHDB - The main wrappper.
  - SHFD - Contains information describing one field.
  - SHRC - Describes one record.  May contain many SHFD chunks.

@{b}Chunks:@{ub}
  - SHDR - Header chunk containing two long words:  the number of fields in
           the database, and the number of records.  There should only be one
           SHDR in a FORM SHDB.
           Note:  ShimmerDB doesn't actually use this chunk yet.  It may one
           day be used, expanded, or completely disposed of.
  - TITL - Title string of a field or record.
  - DSTR - A field or record's data string.
  - TEXT - Standard TEXT chunk containing ASCII data.  Used for multi-line
           text.

@{b}A typical file:@{ub}
  FORM SHDB
    SHDR              - Header chunk.

    FORM SHFD         - These SHFD chunks describe
      TITL              the database's fields.
      DSTR
    FORM SHFD
      TITL            - Field title.
      DSTR            - Field data (optional).
    FORM SHFD
      TITL
      DSTR

    FORM SHRC         - Now the records...
      TITL            - The record's name.
      FORM SHFD       - Records may contain many fields, or none.
        TITL          - Which field.
        DSTR          - The field's data.
      FORM SHFD
        TITL
        TEXT          - This field contains multi-line text, but no DSTR.
    FORM SHRC
      TITL            - This record has no data.
    FORM SHRC
      .
      .
      .               - ...And so on.
@endnode

@node CLIP "ShimmerDB:  Clipboard"

@{u}@{b}ClipBoard Information:@{ub}@{uu}
  When data is copied from a database to the clipboard it is stored as an IFF
CAT CLIP containing two FORMs.  The first FORM will be ShimmerDB's native
@{"FORM SHDB" link FORM}, the second FORM FTXT.

  Within the FORM FTXT will be multiple CHRS chunks.  Assuming a record was
copied, the clipboard data will appear as:
  FORM FTXT
    CHRS  - Record name.
    CHRS  - Field name (if the field holds any data).
    CHRS  - Field data.
    CHRS  - Multiline text (if present).
    .
    .
    .     - and so on.


  When data is copied from the clipboard into a database ShimmerDB will first
look for a FORM SHDB.  If one is found, then data is inserted with fields
being indexed if the name already exists, and records obeying the options
selected in the @{"Settings->Insert/Append" link MN_STNG} menu.  I'm not
satisfied with this behavior; it will probably change in future versions.
  If no FORM SHDB is found, then FORM FTXT is searched for and used.  Any FTXT
data is used as field or record names (if the edit type selected is "Fields" or
"Records").


  CAT CLIP
    FORM SHDB
      <whatever...>
      Note:  The SHDR chunk will most likely be inaccurate.  This will either
      be fixed in a future version, or the SHDB chunk will be abandoned
      totally.
    FORM FTXT
      <CHRS chunks...>
@endnode

@node BUGS "ShimmerDB:  Known Bugs"

@{u}@{b}Bugs:@{ub}@{uu}
  At present, all known bugs have been corrected (or so they'd like me to
believe...).

  If you find a bug, please report it.  When reporting bugs, be as descriptive
as possible about the problem, and what steps lead to it. Details of your
system (CPU, amount of RAM, OS version, other programs running at the time,
etc.) would also be useful.

  See @{"The Author" link SMEGHEAD} for mailing addresses.
@endnode

@node ODD "ShimmerDB:  'There's somethin' screwy goin' on here...'"

@{u}@{b}Oddities:@{ub}@{uu}
  These aren't serious enough to be called bugs, but they could use some
improvement.

  - Tab cycling between string gadgets could be smoother.  <Return> and
   <Shift><Return> work much better.

  - Using menu shortcuts from within string gadgets is a little dodgy.

  - In search patterns, maybe leading and trailing "*" wildcards should be
   implied to find partial strings?  Judgement call; right now I'm thinking,
   "no."

  - Clipboard pasting isn't as smooth as it could/should be.

  - Clipboard operations haven't been extensively tested yet; there may be
   bugs here (why not, they've creeped up everywhere else :-) ) - let me know.

  - Save often in low memory situations; ShimmerDB's default behavior is to
   exit (safely) when memory allocation fails.  This will be improved.

  - These docs (and you're reading the _improved_ version).  :-)
@endnode

@node TODO "ShimmerDB:  The Next Generation"

@{b}Things to do@{ub} (listed in no particular order)@{b}:@{ub}

  - ARexx interface. *
  - Handle multiple projects/views.
  - Printing.
  - Localization.
  - Hide user-specified records and/or fields.
  - An auto-executing field type.  Maybe two or three (execute whenever the
   current field, a specified field, or any field is modified).
  - More field-type control sequences.  Let me know what you'd like to see.
  - Interface enhancements (some things worked better in theory than in
   practice).  Possible rewrite using MUI or BGUI.
  - Find bugs, and replace them with newer, more interesting bugs. *
  - Import/export FTXT.
  - Power Packer/XPK support.
  - More, and more descriptive, error messages/requesters.
  - Maybe use style guide compliant "FONTNAME", "FONTSIZE" rather than
   DiskMaster-style <font>/<size>.  Depends on how many complaints I recieve...
  - More editing features when dealing with multi-line text.
  - Install my own string gadget EditHook for clipboard and menu shortcut
   support.  Maybe...
  - Recursion - fields that contain entire databases of their own.
  - Preferences file.
  - User-defined menu(s) to launch ARexx macros.
  - Raise limits to two to four billion items per list.
  - Improved documentation. *
  - AppWindow/AppIcon support.
  - Improve behavior in low memory situations. *


* Priority.
@endnode

